he cried, showing his decrepit clothing. \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]I was \
with\\nthe boys in the Kremlin when the _yunkers_ came the first time. \
They\\nshut me up in the cellar and swiped my overcoat, my money, watch \
and\\neven the ring on my finger. This is all I\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve got to \
wear!\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\\n\\nFrom him I learned many details of the \
