Beginning of World\\nSocial Revolution,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Long Live the Brotherhood of Workers of the\\nWorld.\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\\n\\nA bitter wind swept the Square, lifting the \
banners. Now from the far\\nquarters of the city the workers of the different \
factories were\\narriving, with their dead. They could be seen coming through \
the\\nGate, the blare of their banners, and the dull red--like blood--of \
the\\ncoffins they carried. These were rude boxes, made of unplaned \
