who\\nmarched with tears streaming down their faces, and followed by \
women\\nwho sobbed and screamed, or walked stiffly, with white, dead \
faces.\\nSome of the coffins were open, the lid carried behind them; \
others\\nwere covered with gilded or silvered cloth, or had a soldier\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s hat\\nnailed on the top. There were many wreaths of \
hideous artificial\\nflowers....\\n\\nThrough an irregular lane that opened \
and closed again the procession\\nslowly moved toward us. Now through the \
