all the\\nchurches of the capital, the priests stopped praying for it. But as\
\\nLenin himself told the _Tsay-ee-kah,_ that was \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]only \
the beginning\\nof the conquest of power.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] Deprived of \
arms, the opposition, which\\nstill controlled the economic life of the \
country, settled down to\\norganise disorganisation, with all the Russian \
genius for\\ncooperative action--to obstruct, cripple and discredit the \
